hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider a function $S(t)$ that models the state of a theoretical physical system at time $t$. The behavior of the system is described by one of two different polynomial models, depending on whether the time $t$ is a rational or irrational number.

The function is defined as follows:
$$
S(t) = \begin{cases}
3t^2 - 4t - 2  \text{if } t \in \mathbb{Q} \text{ (the set of rational numbers)} \\
t^2 + 2t + 1  \text{if } t \in \mathbb{R} \setminus \mathbb{Q} \text{ (the set of irrational numbers)}
\end{cases}
$$
Determine the product of all real values of $t$ for which the function $S(t)$ is continuous.
